This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method that involves using external memory, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research, hence cs.AI is also likely. The paper also involves training a model, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), hence cs.LG (Learning) is another likely sub-category. The proposed method involves attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in neural networks, hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on language translation, which can also involve computer vision (CV) techniques, hence cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible sub-category.
